SUMMARY:Magnolia Walk in the Garden
DESCRIPTION:Sundays\, March 22 & 29; April 5 & 12 | 2-3 PM | Free with admission or membership \n\n\n\nJoin one of our gardeners for a guided stroll through Lan Su’s magnolia collection during Magnolia Festival. Beginning at the Mountain Magnolia near the entrance\, we’ll explore several varieties while learning about their history\, cultural significance\, and unique botanical features. \n\n\n\nAlong the way\, take in the seasonal magnolia-inspired floral installations (through March 30) before ending on the Terrace\, where you’ll get to appreciate an original piece of Lan Su history. There\, we’ll take in the recently dedicated Fengchun (鳳春 “Phoenix of Spring”)—a magnolia tree that Suzhou landscape architect Ms. He chose for the garden 25-plus years ago when we first opened. \n\n\n\nBefore you go\, we invite you to stop by Yun Shui Teahouse to enjoy a cup of magnolia tea and truly soak in this special flower! \n\n\n\n\n\nTour Guides\n\n\n\n\nMarch 22 & 29: Ben\, Gardener\n\n\n\nApril 5 & 12: Patrick\, Head Gardener\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMore About Ms. He’s Magnolia Tree\n\n\n\n\n\nMs. He guides the original design of Lan Su with Suzhou artisans.\n\n\n\n\n\nCurator of Horticulture Josie Losh holds a scroll in front of Ms. He’s magnolia tree\, dedicated in September 2025. \n\n\n\n\n\nAs part of Lan Su’s 25th-anniversary celebration in September 2025\, we were honored to rename one of our magnolia trees after Ms. He Fengchun\, former Director of the Suzhou Garden Design Institute. Members of the Suzhou Garden Bureau and Suzhou city administrator delegation joined us for the unveiling ceremony\, continuing decades of cultural exchange with our sister city. \n\n\n\nMs. He was a driving force behind Lan Su’s original design and plant collections\, and Lan Su was her very first garden design project—a connection she treasures deeply. This particular magnolia\, her favorite in the garden\, now bears her name in tribute to her vision and dedication. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAdmission Rates\n\n\n\n\nLan Su Members & Guests: FREE\n\n\n\nAdult: $16.95\n\n\n\nSenior (62+) or Student (18+ with ID): $15.95\n\n\n\nYouth (6-18 yr): $13.95\n\n\n\nChild (5 yr & under): FREE\n\n\n\n\nNote: A $0.95 service fee is reflected in each paid admission. \n\n\n\nDiscounted Admission Offers\n\n\n\nThese offers must be redeemed in person at the Lan Su Ticket Booth to confirm eligibility. \n\n\n\nEBT/WIC Cardholders\n\n\n\nDiscounted admission of $5.00 per person is available for up to four individuals per EBT/WIC card. To claim this offer\, please present your EBT/WIC card and a valid form of photo ID at the Ticket Booth. \n\n\n\nVeterans & Military\n\n\n\nWe offer $2 off admission for active-duty military\, veterans\, and their immediate family members with valid ID. The discount must be redeemed in person at the Ticket Booth. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nParking & Directions\n\n\n\nFree Lan Su Parking\n\n\n\nThere is free first come\, first served parking in our sister lot next to the garden at 424 NW Third Avenue. Additional metered parking and garages are available on surrounding streets.
URL:https://lansugarden.org/event/magnolia-walk-in-the-garden/2026-03-29/
LOCATION:Lan Su Chinese Garden\, 239 NW Everett Street\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209
CATEGORIES:Free with admission or membership,Horticulture,Magnolia Festival
